text:
     A permit to convert shall be denied by Director of the Department of Building Inspection if: 
     (a)     The requirements of Sections 
41.12 or 
41.13, above, have not been fully complied with;
     (b)     The application is incomplete or contains incorrect information;
     (c)     An applicant has committed unlawful action as defined in this Chapter within 12 months previous to the issuance for a permit to convert; 
     (d)     The proposed conversion or the use to which the unit would be converted is not permitted by the City Planning Code.
(Added by Ord. 121-90, App. 4/12/90; amended by Ord. 134-01, File No. 001926, App. 7/6/2001)
